solution.p:

(a) Finding the equivalent reading in Celsius scale requires a direct application of the formula relating Celsius and Fahrenheit given above.


	F=\dfrac{9}{5}C + 32 \Longrightarrow C =\dfrac{5}{9} (F-32)  = 36.7^{\circ}\text{C}

The reading T in Kelvin scale is obtained by simply adding  273.15 to the Celsius reading.

	T = 36.7+273.15 = 309.9\ \text{K}
